{"id": 243283264, "title": "In eventful day, Akron man arrested twice in University Heights for theft", "text": "UNIVERSITY HEIGHTS, Ohio -- Once was not enough for an Akron man who was arrested twice in one eventful day that also included a trip to the hospital. At 1 p.m. June 21, loss prevention personnel at Macy\u2019s, 2201 Warrensville Center Road, reported that it had detained a shoplifting suspect, the 55-year-old Akron man. After he was caught in the act, the man stated he was having a medical emergency. EMS was called to the scene to treat the suspect, who was charged by police with theft. The stolen merchandise totaled $694.79. Police gave the man a Shaker Heights Municipal Court date of July 10 prior to the fire department transporting him to a hospital. Later the same day, at 3:55 p.m., police received a call from the manager of Green Road Liquor, 2181 S. Green Road, who reported that someone was in the process of stealing items. That \u201csomeone\u201d was the Akron man, who had concealed six bottles of liquor in a reusable shopping bag he carried into the store. The stolen goods, this time, totaled $359.94. The man, it was found, had forcefully removed security caps from the bottles. Police once more cited the man for theft and issued him another court date. This time, there was no medical problem. Read more from the Sun Press.", "summary": "University Heights police arrested the same man twice for theft in one day at two different stores. The man's day also included a trip to the hospital.", "url": "https://www.cleveland.com/community/2024/06/in-eventful-day-akron-man-arrested-twice-in-university-heights-for-theft.html", "image": "https://www.cleveland.com/resizer/v2/OU3FAUQQEZAT3EAE72IV7O26LI.jpg?auth=a3d69c806eb13e47ef9f94bfb94a11f385f262458363bcbe5d1fa12f150ad646&width=1280&quality=90", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-29 03:21:35", "author": "Jeff Piorkowski", "authors": ["Jeff Piorkowski"], "language": "en", "source_country": "US", "sentiment": -0.498}